            "question": "What does the print() function do?",
            "options": [
              { "id": "a", "text": "Output content to the screen" },
              { "id": "b", "text": "Read user input" },
              { "id": "c", "text": "Define a variable" },
              { "id": "d", "text": "Perform math" }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": "a",
            "explanation": "The print() function outputs the content inside the parentheses to the screen (console). It is one of the most commonly used functions in Python.",
