    {
      "pageId": "page-variables",
      "title": "Variables",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "block-var-intro",
          "position": { "order": 0 },
          "style": { "spacing": "md", "alignment": "left" },
          "content": {
            "format": "markdown",
            "value": "## What is a variable?\n\nA variable is like a **box** that can store data.\n\nYou can give this box a name and put data inside it."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "codeBlock",
          "id": "block-var-example",
          "position": { "order": 1 },
          "style": { "spacing": "md", "alignment": "left" },
          "content": {
            "language": "python",
            "code": "# Create variables\nname = \"Alex\"    # string type\nage = 18         # integer type\nheight = 1.75    # float type\n\n# Print variables\nprint(name)\nprint(age)\nprint(height)"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "block-var-rules",
          "position": { "order": 2 },
          "style": { "spacing": "md", "alignment": "left" },
          "content": {
            "format": "markdown",
            "value": "### Variable naming rules\n\n1. Can contain letters, numbers, and underscore `_`\n2. Cannot start with a number\n3. Case-sensitive (`name` and `Name` are different)\n4. Cannot use Python keywords (e.g., `if`, `for`, `print`)"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "codePlayground",
          "id": "block-var-practice",
          "position": { "order": 3 },
          "style": { "spacing": "md", "alignment": "left" },
          "content": {
            "language": "python",
            "initialCode": "# Exercise: create a variable x with value 10, then print it\n# Write your code below:\n\n",
            "expectedOutput": "10",
            "hints": [
              "Step 1: x = 10",
              "Step 2: print(x)",
              "Full answer:\nx = 10\nprint(x)"
            ],
            "runnable": true
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "fillBlank",
          "id": "block-var-fill",
          "position": { "order": 4 },
          "style": { "spacing": "md", "alignment": "left" },
          "content": {
            "question": "In Python, use ______ to assign a value to a variable",
            "correctAnswer": "=",
            "hint": "This is a single equals sign, not double equals"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
